content.description: AS PER ORDER FROM THE ARMY CORPS OF ENGINEERS, THIS WALL IS CLOSED TO CLIMBING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE. PLEASE DO NOT CLIMB HERE.Start in the same corner as Severely Rational. Follow thin cracks up and right off the ground to gain the laser cut, thin crack. Lower angled rock above leads up and slightly left to a left-angling crack and overhang. An odd cross-through move past a bolt at the overhang leads up left then back right to a scoop (slightly runout but easy). Exit the scoop on the right, and make hard move up and left to the anchors.
content.protection: This is a mixed gear climb. The cruxes are well protected by bolts.
content.location: Start in the same corner as Severely Rational.

content.description: AS PER ORDER FROM THE ARMY CORPS OF ENGINEERS, THIS WALL IS CLOSED TO CLIMBING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE. PLEASE DO NOT CLIMB HERE.Look for a gold painted bolt in a small alcove on a shallow left-facing corner. Stick clip recommended for the first bolt. Climb to a second bolt and traverse left to a seam and then to the right at a third bolt to gain a slabby left-leaning ramp/corner. Follow the corner up fun easier flakes to a bolted anchor right of a large tree. A fun route with good protection and an easier way to get up to the upper tier of the Corps Wall.
content.protection: A single rack of small cams to 2". A rack of nuts and a few draws for the bolts.
content.location: Look for a small alcove on a shallow left-facing corner with a gold painted bolt. There is a tree right at the start of the route.

content.description: AS PER ORDER FROM THE ARMY CORPS OF ENGINEERS, THIS WALL IS CLOSED TO CLIMBING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE. PLEASE DO NOT CLIMB HERE.Photo 51 is the rightmost route of Corps Wall.Follow an overlap (small cam placement) to a corner. Clip two bolts just below a roof. Pull the roof to two more bolts. Climb up to a thin horizontal (micro cams) to the anchor.
content.protection: A singles rack from micros to a #2, 4 bolts, and a 2 bolt anchor.

content.description: AS PER ORDER FROM THE ARMY CORPS OF ENGINEERS, THIS WALL IS CLOSED TO CLIMBING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE. PLEASE DO NOT CLIMB HERE.
content.location: It is on the left side of the wall, halfway up the hill on your way to Economy of Motion.

content.description: AS PER ORDER FROM THE ARMY CORPS OF ENGINEERS, THIS WALL IS CLOSED TO CLIMBING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE. PLEASE DO NOT CLIMB HERE.Start at the left corner of the pillar, and climb the offwidth on the right side all the way to the anchor.
content.protection: Cams #3, 4, 5 are very helpful on this route.
content.location: It ascends the obvious offwidth on the right side of the pillar.

content.description: AS PER ORDER FROM THE ARMY CORPS OF ENGINEERS, THIS WALL IS CLOSED TO CLIMBING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE. PLEASE DO NOT CLIMB HERE.Climb up the slab to a stance below the right-angling crack. Follow the crack, and make a committing reach (crux) to the top. Traverse right on a rail. Finish by heading up right towards the bolted anchor.
content.location: Begin on the dirty slab below the right-angling crack above.

content.description: AS PER ORDER FROM THE ARMY CORPS OF ENGINEERS, THIS WALL IS CLOSED TO CLIMBING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE. PLEASE DO NOT CLIMB HERE.Climb high up onto a ledge. Place a 0.5 cam, and mantel just below the first bolt. Follow thin moves along an angling seam.There is a big move at the end (well protected by the last bolt). Me, 5'1", could get it by a dyno.
content.protection: This is a well bolted route. You can place an optional 0.5 below the first bolt.
content.location: Start from the ledge right next to "Double Standard Left."
